{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01JXWoFRza7z5eyis7TKZDcB","type":"tool_result","content":"# lifecycle API\n\nPurpose: Defines the HTTP request and response contract for all five lifecycle endpoints. Covers user registration, retrieval, deletion, login, and logout.\n\nTags: architecture, design\n\n## POST /users\n\nRegister a new user.\n\n**Request body:**\n```json\n{\"username\": \"string\", \"password\": \"string\"}\n```\n\n**Responses:**\n- `201 Created` — `{\"id\": \"string\", \"username\": \"string\"}`\n- `400 Bad Request` — missing fields, empty values, or username already taken\n\nThe response body never includes the password or password hash.\n\n## GET /users/{id}\n\nRetrieve a user by ID.\n\n**Responses:**\n- `200 OK` — `{\"id\": \"string\", \"username\": \"string\"}`\n- `404 Not Found` — no user with that ID\n\n## DELETE /users/{id}\n\nDelete a user and invalidate all tokens belonging to that user.\n\n**Responses:**\n- `200 OK` — empty body\n- `404 Not Found` — no user with that ID\n\n## POST /auth/login\n\nAuthenticate a user and issue an opaque session token.\n\n**Request body:**\n```json\n{\"username\": \"string\", \"password\": \"string\"}\n```\n\n**Responses:**\n- `200 OK` — `{\"token\": \"string\"}`\n- `401 Unauthorized` — unknown username or wrong password\n\n## POST /auth/logout\n\nInvalidate a session token.\n\n**Request header:** `Authorization: Bearer <token>`\n\n**Responses:**\n- `200 OK` — empty body\n- `401 Unauthorized` — missing `Authorization` header, wrong scheme, or unknown/already-invalidated token","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2fb6b9dc-abcb-47da-b867-a61b57d726b7","uuid":"d2fde4fa-94d6-4eb9-b6f7-54f017849059","timestamp":"2026-04-05T09:19:36.545Z","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"# lifecycle API\n\nPurpose: Defines the HTTP request and response contract for all five lifecycle endpoints. Covers user registration, retrieval, deletion, login, and logout.\n\nTags: architecture, design\n\n## POST /users\n\nRegister a new user.\n\n**Request body:**\n```json\n{\"username\": \"string\", \"password\": \"string\"}\n```\n\n**Responses:**\n- `201 Created` — `{\"id\": \"string\", \"username\": \"string\"}`\n- `400 Bad Request` — missing fields, empty values, or username already taken\n\nThe response body never includes the password or password hash.\n\n## GET /users/{id}\n\nRetrieve a user by ID.\n\n**Responses:**\n- `200 OK` — `{\"id\": \"string\", \"username\": \"string\"}`\n- `404 Not Found` — no user with that ID\n\n## DELETE /users/{id}\n\nDelete a user and invalidate all tokens belonging to that user.\n\n**Responses:**\n- `200 OK` — empty body\n- `404 Not Found` — no user with that ID\n\n## POST /auth/login\n\nAuthenticate a user and issue an opaque session token.\n\n**Request body:**\n```json\n{\"username\": \"string\", \"password\": \"string\"}\n```\n\n**Responses:**\n- `200 OK` — `{\"token\": \"string\"}`\n- `401 Unauthorized` — unknown username or wrong password\n\n## POST /auth/logout\n\nInvalidate a session token.\n\n**Request header:** `Authorization: Bearer <token>`\n\n**Responses:**\n- `200 OK` — empty body\n- `401 Unauthorized` — missing `Authorization` header, wrong scheme, or unknown/already-invalidated token","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01RauFKXcDbLGdGYwzhB4XKe","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a clear picture of the design. Let me design the `authz` component:\n\n1. **Package**: `authz` at `internal/iam/authz`\n2. **Language**: Go\n3. **Stores**:\n   - `RoleStore`: `map[string]Role` protected by `sync.RWMutex`\n   - `UserRoles`: `map[string][]string` (userID → []roleID) protected by `sync.RWMutex`\n4. **Role struct**: `{id, name string, permissions []string}`\n\n\n5. **Endpoints**: I'll expose role creation and listing, user role assignment and retrieval, and a permission check endpoint that returns whether an action is allowed\n6. **Public entry point**: `Handler()` returns `*http.ServeMux`\n7. **Module target**: Go 1.21, so I'll stick with standard patterns since method-prefix patterns aren't available\n8. **ID generation**: Using `github.com/google/uuid` for generating unique identifiers\n9. No external dependencies beyond that\n\nFor the `POST /users/{id}/roles` endpoint, a 404 means the specified roleId doesn't exist—since authz is self-contained and can't validate against the lifecycle store, I only need to check if the role itself is known. The userId in the path doesn't require validation. For `GET /users/{id}/roles`, I'll always return 200 with whatever roles are assigned to that user, even if it's an empty list.\n\nThe `POST /authz/check` endpoint always responds with 200, returning `{\"allowed\": false}` when the user has no roles or the permission isn't found.\n\nNow I'm setting up the implementation files—defining the role and user role structures, the store, handlers for all five endpoints, and comprehensive table-driven tests. After that I'll write the documentation files and finalize the response.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":818,"cache_read_input_tokens":22230,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":818},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2fb6b9dc-abcb-47da-b867-a61b57d726b7","uuid":"ae937ad7-a4ac-4ad7-a9a1-b9fbb94fab7f"}
