{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01RauFKXcDbLGdGYwzhB4XKe","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01DP7xCHPoP1UTWLrWD5Uwfh","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/david/Go/src/github.com/cornjacket/ai-builder/acceptance-spec/sandbox/regressions/platform-monolith/output/internal/iam/internal/iam/authz/README.md","content":"# authz\n\nPurpose: Provides in-memory role management and RBAC permission checks for the IAM listener. Implements five HTTP endpoints exposed via an `*http.ServeMux` for registration by integrate-iam.\n\nTags: architecture, design\n\n## File Index\n\n| File | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| `authz.go` | `Role` struct, `Store` (RoleStore + UserRoles), `handler` struct, `Handler()` constructor, all five HTTP handler methods |\n| `authz_test.go` | Table-driven HTTP tests for all five endpoints using `net/http/httptest` |\n\n## Overview\n\nThe package owns two in-memory stores, both protected by a single `sync.RWMutex`:\n\n- **RoleStore** — `map[string]Role` keyed by role ID, holding `{id, name string, permissions []string}` records.\n- **UserRoles** — `map[string][]string` keyed by user ID, holding a slice of role IDs assigned to that user.\n\nRole IDs are generated with `github.com/google/uuid` (v4). All response bodies are JSON; errors use `{\"error\":\"<message>\"}`.\n\n`Handler()` is the single public entry point. It constructs the store, wires it into a private `handler` struct, and returns a `*http.ServeMux` with all five routes registered. Because the module targets Go 1.21, method-prefix patterns (`POST /roles`) are not available — the mux registers bare paths and each handler switches on `r.Method`. Path parameters for `/users/{id}/roles` are extracted by splitting `r.URL.Path`.\n\n### Permission Check Logic\n\n`POST /authz/check` looks up the user's assigned role IDs in UserRoles, then for each role ID fetches the Role from RoleStore and scans its `permissions` slice. It returns `{\"allowed\":true}` on the first match, `{\"allowed\":false}` if none match or the user has no assigned roles. Roles that no longer exist in RoleStore are silently skipped during the walk.\n\n### 404 Semantics for Role Assignment\n\n`POST /users/{id}/roles` validates that the `roleId` field in the request body refers to an existing role in RoleStore. If the role is not found it returns 404. The `{id}` user path parameter is not validated against any external store — authz has no compile-time dependency on lifecycle.\n\n### Dependencies\n\n- `github.com/google/uuid` — already in `go.mod`; used for role ID generation\n\nSee [api.md](api.md) for the full endpoint contract.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":818,"cache_read_input_tokens":22230,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":818},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2fb6b9dc-abcb-47da-b867-a61b57d726b7","uuid":"7ed7313b-662f-48c3-865b-b691866647b6"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01DP7xCHPoP1UTWLrWD5Uwfh","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /Users/david/Go/src/github.com/cornjacket/ai-builder/acceptance-spec/sandbox/regressions/platform-monolith/output/internal/iam/internal/iam/authz/README.md has been updated successfully."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2fb6b9dc-abcb-47da-b867-a61b57d726b7","uuid":"38bb156c-51d8-4a22-8bac-27b7a866e373","timestamp":"2026-04-05T09:19:57.778Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"update","filePath":"/Users/david/Go/src/github.com/cornjacket/ai-builder/acceptance-spec/sandbox/regressions/platform-monolith/output/internal/iam/internal/iam/authz/README.md","content":"# authz\n\nPurpose: Provides in-memory role management and RBAC permission checks for the IAM listener. Implements five HTTP endpoints exposed via an `*http.ServeMux` for registration by integrate-iam.\n\nTags: architecture, design\n\n## File Index\n\n| File | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| `authz.go` | `Role` struct, `Store` (RoleStore + UserRoles), `handler` struct, `Handler()` constructor, all five HTTP handler methods |\n| `authz_test.go` | Table-driven HTTP tests for all five endpoints using `net/http/httptest` |\n\n## Overview\n\nThe package owns two in-memory stores, both protected by a single `sync.RWMutex`:\n\n- **RoleStore** — `map[string]Role` keyed by role ID, holding `{id, name string, permissions []string}` records.\n- **UserRoles** — `map[string][]string` keyed by user ID, holding a slice of role IDs assigned to that user.\n\nRole IDs are generated with `github.com/google/uuid` (v4). All response bodies are JSON; errors use `{\"error\":\"<message>\"}`.\n\n`Handler()` is the single public entry point. It constructs the store, wires it into a private `handler` struct, and returns a `*http.ServeMux` with all five routes registered. Because the module targets Go 1.21, method-prefix patterns (`POST /roles`) are not available — the mux registers bare paths and each handler switches on `r.Method`. Path parameters for `/users/{id}/roles` are extracted by splitting `r.URL.Path`.\n\n### Permission Check Logic\n\n`POST /authz/check` looks up the user's assigned role IDs in UserRoles, then for each role ID fetches the Role from RoleStore and scans its `permissions` slice. It returns `{\"allowed\":true}` on the first match, `{\"allowed\":false}` if none match or the user has no assigned roles. Roles that no longer exist in RoleStore are silently skipped during the walk.\n\n### 404 Semantics for Role Assignment\n\n`POST /users/{id}/roles` validates that the `roleId` field in the request body refers to an existing role in RoleStore. If the role is not found it returns 404. The `{id}` user path parameter is not validated against any external store — authz has no compile-time dependency on lifecycle.\n\n### Dependencies\n\n- `github.com/google/uuid` — already in `go.mod`; used for role ID generation\n\nSee [api.md](api.md) for the full endpoint contract.\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":1,"oldLines":3,"newStart":1,"newLines":37,"lines":[" # authz"," ","-_Placeholder. ARCHITECT fills in documentation._","+Purpose: Provides in-memory role management and RBAC permission checks for the IAM listener. Implements five HTTP endpoints exposed via an `*http.ServeMux` for registration by integrate-iam.","+","+Tags: architecture, design","+","+## File Index","+","+| File | Description |","+|------|-------------|","+| `authz.go` | `Role` struct, `Store` (RoleStore + UserRoles), `handler` struct, `Handler()` constructor, all five HTTP handler methods |","+| `authz_test.go` | Table-driven HTTP tests for all five endpoints using `net/http/httptest` |","+","+## Overview","+","+The package owns two in-memory stores, both protected by a single `sync.RWMutex`:","+","+- **RoleStore** — `map[string]Role` keyed by role ID, holding `{id, name string, permissions []string}` records.","+- **UserRoles** — `map[string][]string` keyed by user ID, holding a slice of role IDs assigned to that user.","+","+Role IDs are generated with `github.com/google/uuid` (v4). All response bodies are JSON; errors use `{\"error\":\"<message>\"}`.","+","+`Handler()` is the single public entry point. It constructs the store, wires it into a private `handler` struct, and returns a `*http.ServeMux` with all five routes registered. Because the module targets Go 1.21, method-prefix patterns (`POST /roles`) are not available — the mux registers bare paths and each handler switches on `r.Method`. Path parameters for `/users/{id}/roles` are extracted by splitting `r.URL.Path`.","+","+### Permission Check Logic","+","+`POST /authz/check` looks up the user's assigned role IDs in UserRoles, then for each role ID fetches the Role from RoleStore and scans its `permissions` slice. It returns `{\"allowed\":true}` on the first match, `{\"allowed\":false}` if none match or the user has no assigned roles. Roles that no longer exist in RoleStore are silently skipped during the walk.","+","+### 404 Semantics for Role Assignment","+","+`POST /users/{id}/roles` validates that the `roleId` field in the request body refers to an existing role in RoleStore. If the role is not found it returns 404. The `{id}` user path parameter is not validated against any external store — authz has no compile-time dependency on lifecycle.","+","+### Dependencies","+","+- `github.com/google/uuid` — already in `go.mod`; used for role ID generation","+","+See [api.md](api.md) for the full endpoint contract."]}],"originalFile":"# authz\n\n_Placeholder. ARCHITECT fills in documentation._\n"}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_015i5zpW8CMB9NrNChvT4oq4","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_018bT3Zh1QaiRFqFZxci15Wi","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/david/Go/src/github.com/cornjacket/ai-builder/acceptance-spec/sandbox/regressions/platform-monolith/output/internal/iam/internal/iam/authz/api.md","content":"# authz API\n\nPurpose: Defines the HTTP request and response contract for all five authz endpoints. Covers role creation, role listing, role assignment, user-role retrieval, and permission checking.\n\nTags: architecture, design\n\n## POST /roles\n\nCreate a new role.\n\n**Request body:**\n```json\n{\"name\": \"string\", \"permissions\": [\"string\"]}\n```\n\n**Responses:**\n- `201 Created` — `{\"id\": \"string\", \"name\": \"string\", \"permissions\": [\"string\"]}`\n- `400 Bad Request` — missing or empty `name` field, or body cannot be decoded\n\n`permissions` may be an empty array. The response echoes the stored role including the generated `id`.\n\n## GET /roles\n\nList all roles.\n\n**Responses:**\n- `200 OK` — `[{\"id\": \"string\", \"name\": \"string\", \"permissions\": [\"string\"]}]`\n\nReturns an empty JSON array `[]` when no roles exist. Never returns 404.\n\n## POST /users/{id}/roles\n\nAssign an existing role to a user.\n\n**Path parameter:** `{id}` — the user ID (not validated against lifecycle; any string is accepted as a user identifier)\n\n**Request body:**\n```json\n{\"roleId\": \"string\"}\n```\n\n**Responses:**\n- `201 Created` — empty body; the role has been added to the user's role list\n- `404 Not Found` — `roleId` does not refer to an existing role in RoleStore\n- `400 Bad Request` — body cannot be decoded or `roleId` is empty\n\nAssigning the same role to a user twice is idempotent — a second assignment still returns 201 but does not create a duplicate entry.\n\n## GET /users/{id}/roles\n\nRetrieve all roles assigned to a user.\n\n**Path parameter:** `{id}` — the user ID\n\n**Responses:**\n- `200 OK` — `[{\"id\": \"string\", \"name\": \"string\", \"permissions\": [\"string\"]}]`\n\nReturns an empty JSON array `[]` when the user has no assigned roles or the user ID is unknown. Never returns 404.\n\n## POST /authz/check\n\nCheck whether a user has a specific permission.\n\n**Request body:**\n```json\n{\"userId\": \"string\", \"permission\": \"string\"}\n```\n\n**Responses:**\n- `200 OK` — `{\"allowed\": true}` or `{\"allowed\": false}`\n- `400 Bad Request` — body cannot be decoded\n\nAlways returns 200. Returns `{\"allowed\": false}` when the user has no assigned roles, when none of the assigned roles exist in RoleStore, or when no role's permissions slice contains the requested permission string.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1482,"cache_read_input_tokens":23048,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1482},"output_tokens":72,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2fb6b9dc-abcb-47da-b867-a61b57d726b7","uuid":"3e28e398-0788-4375-8179-a082c6b138ef"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_018bT3Zh1QaiRFqFZxci15Wi","type":"tool_result","content":"File created successfully at: /Users/david/Go/src/github.com/cornjacket/ai-builder/acceptance-spec/sandbox/regressions/platform-monolith/output/internal/iam/internal/iam/authz/api.md"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2fb6b9dc-abcb-47da-b867-a61b57d726b7","uuid":"a77cc34a-ada0-4630-8879-59364d2a18ea","timestamp":"2026-04-05T09:20:08.284Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"create","filePath":"/Users/david/Go/src/github.com/cornjacket/ai-builder/acceptance-spec/sandbox/regressions/platform-monolith/output/internal/iam/internal/iam/authz/api.md","content":"# authz API\n\nPurpose: Defines the HTTP request and response contract for all five authz endpoints. Covers role creation, role listing, role assignment, user-role retrieval, and permission checking.\n\nTags: architecture, design\n\n## POST /roles\n\nCreate a new role.\n\n**Request body:**\n```json\n{\"name\": \"string\", \"permissions\": [\"string\"]}\n```\n\n**Responses:**\n- `201 Created` — `{\"id\": \"string\", \"name\": \"string\", \"permissions\": [\"string\"]}`\n- `400 Bad Request` — missing or empty `name` field, or body cannot be decoded\n\n`permissions` may be an empty array. The response echoes the stored role including the generated `id`.\n\n## GET /roles\n\nList all roles.\n\n**Responses:**\n- `200 OK` — `[{\"id\": \"string\", \"name\": \"string\", \"permissions\": [\"string\"]}]`\n\nReturns an empty JSON array `[]` when no roles exist. Never returns 404.\n\n## POST /users/{id}/roles\n\nAssign an existing role to a user.\n\n**Path parameter:** `{id}` — the user ID (not validated against lifecycle; any string is accepted as a user identifier)\n\n**Request body:**\n```json\n{\"roleId\": \"string\"}\n```\n\n**Responses:**\n- `201 Created` — empty body; the role has been added to the user's role list\n- `404 Not Found` — `roleId` does not refer to an existing role in RoleStore\n- `400 Bad Request` — body cannot be decoded or `roleId` is empty\n\nAssigning the same role to a user twice is idempotent — a second assignment still returns 201 but does not create a duplicate entry.\n\n## GET /users/{id}/roles\n\nRetrieve all roles assigned to a user.\n\n**Path parameter:** `{id}` — the user ID\n\n**Responses:**\n- `200 OK` — `[{\"id\": \"string\", \"name\": \"string\", \"permissions\": [\"string\"]}]`\n\nReturns an empty JSON array `[]` when the user has no assigned roles or the user ID is unknown. Never returns 404.\n\n## POST /authz/check\n\nCheck whether a user has a specific permission.\n\n**Request body:**\n```json\n{\"userId\": \"string\", \"permission\": \"string\"}\n```\n\n**Responses:**\n- `200 OK` — `{\"allowed\": true}` or `{\"allowed\": false}`\n- `400 Bad Request` — body cannot be decoded\n\nAlways returns 200. Returns `{\"allowed\": false}` when the user has no assigned roles, when none of the assigned roles exist in RoleStore, or when no role's permissions slice contains the requested permission string.\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_017ietLfs6HYzEsjUSehfosY","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"<response>\n  <outcome>ARCHITECT_DESIGN_READY</outcome>\n  <handoff>The authz package is a single-file Go component at internal/iam/authz. It owns two in-memory stores — RoleStore (map[string]Role) and UserRoles (map[string][]string) — both guarded by one sync.RWMutex on the handler struct. Handler() is the sole public entry point, returning a *http.ServeMux with five routes registered as bare paths (Go 1.21; no method-prefix mux patterns). Role IDs are uuid.New().String(). POST /users/{id}/roles returns 404 when the roleId is not in RoleStore (user ID is not validated). POST /authz/check always returns 200 with {\"allowed\":bool}; the walk skips stale role IDs silently. Only dependency is github.com/google/uuid, already in go.mod. One source file (authz.go) and one test file (authz_test.go).</handoff>\n  <documents_written>true</documents_written>\n  <design>\n## Design\n\n**Language:** Go (same module as lifecycle; targets Go 1.21)\n\n**Package path:** `internal/iam/authz`\n\n**Files to produce:**\n- `authz.go` — all types, stores, constructor, and handler methods\n- `authz_test.go` — table-driven httptest-based tests for all five endpoints\n\n### Data model\n\n```go\ntype Role struct {\n    ID          string   `json:\"id\"`\n    Name        string   `json:\"name\"`\n    Permissions []string `json:\"permissions\"`\n}\n```\n\n### Store and handler struct\n\n```go\ntype handler struct {\n    mu        sync.RWMutex\n    roleStore map[string]Role     // keyed by role ID\n    userRoles map[string][]string // keyed by user ID → []roleID\n}\n```\n\nA single `sync.RWMutex` guards both maps. Read-only operations (GET /roles, GET /users/{id}/roles, POST /authz/check) acquire `RLock`; write operations (POST /roles, POST /users/{id}/roles) acquire the full `Lock`.\n\n### Handler() constructor\n\n```go\nfunc Handler() *http.ServeMux {\n    h := &handler{\n        roleStore: make(map[string]Role),\n        userRoles: make(map[string][]string),\n    }\n    mux := http.NewServeMux()\n    mux.HandleFunc(\"/roles\", h.handleRoles)\n    mux.HandleFunc(\"/users/\", h.handleUsers)   // catches /users/{id}/roles\n    mux.HandleFunc(\"/authz/check\", h.handleAuthzCheck)\n    return mux\n}\n```\n\n`/users/` uses a trailing-slash prefix match so one handler covers both `POST /users/{id}/roles` and `GET /users/{id}/roles`. The handler splits `r.URL.Path` on `/` to extract the user ID and confirm the path suffix is `roles`.\n\n### Endpoint logic\n\n**POST /roles:** decode body; reject empty `name` with 400; generate uuid ID; store in roleStore; respond 201 with full Role JSON.\n\n**GET /roles:** acquire RLock; iterate roleStore; collect into a `[]Role` slice (stable iteration order not required); respond 200 with JSON array (empty array `[]` if none).\n\n**POST /users/{id}/roles:** decode body; reject empty `roleId` with 400; acquire Lock; look up roleId in roleStore — if missing respond 404; append roleId to userRoles[userID] only if not already present (idempotent); respond 201 with empty body.\n\n**GET /users/{id}/roles:** acquire RLock; look up userRoles[userID] (empty slice if absent); for each roleID fetch from roleStore (skip if missing); collect into `[]Role`; respond 200 with JSON array.\n\n**POST /authz/check:** decode body; acquire RLock; look up userRoles[userId]; for each roleID fetch from roleStore (skip missing); scan `permissions` slice for exact string match; return 200 `{\"allowed\":true}` on first match, `{\"allowed\":false}` if exhausted.\n\n### Error responses\n\nAll error bodies: `{\"error\":\"<message>\"}` with appropriate status code. `POST /authz/check` never returns 404 — unknown users yield `{\"allowed\":false}`.\n\n### Dependencies\n\n- `github.com/google/uuid` — already in go.mod\n- stdlib only otherwise (`encoding/json`, `net/http`, `strings`, `sync`)\n  </design>\n  <acceptance_criteria>\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n1. `POST /roles` with `{\"name\":\"admin\",\"permissions\":[\"read\",\"write\"]}` returns 201 and a JSON body containing `\"name\":\"admin\"`, `\"permissions\":[\"read\",\"write\"]`, and a non-empty `\"id\"` string.\n2. `POST /roles` with a missing `name` field (e.g. `{}`) returns 400.\n3. `GET /roles` returns 200 with a JSON array; after creating two roles the array contains exactly two entries matching the created roles.\n4. `GET /roles` before any role is created returns 200 with an empty JSON array `[]`.\n5. `POST /users/u1/roles` with `{\"roleId\":\"<id of existing role>\"}` returns 201.\n6. `POST /users/u1/roles` with `{\"roleId\":\"nonexistent-id\"}` returns 404.\n7. `GET /users/u1/roles` after assigning one role to u1 returns 200 with a one-element array containing that role's full object.\n8. `GET /users/u1/roles` for a user with no assigned roles returns 200 with an empty array `[]`.\n9. `POST /authz/check` with `{\"userId\":\"u1\",\"permission\":\"read\"}` returns 200 `{\"allowed\":true}` when u1 has been assigned a role whose permissions include `\"read\"`.\n10. `POST /authz/check` with `{\"userId\":\"u1\",\"permission\":\"delete\"}` returns 200 `{\"allowed\":false}` when no assigned role contains `\"delete\"`.\n11. `POST /authz/check` with an unknown `userId` returns 200 `{\"allowed\":false}`.\n12. Assigning the same role to a user twice via `POST /users/{id}/roles` results in the role appearing exactly once in `GET /users/{id}/roles`.\n  </acceptance_criteria>\n  <test_command>cd /Users/david/Go/src/github.com/cornjacket/ai-builder/acceptance-spec/sandbox/regressions/platform-monolith/output/internal/iam/internal/iam/authz && go test ./...</test_command>\n</response>"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":820,"cache_read_input_tokens":24530,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":820},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2fb6b9dc-abcb-47da-b867-a61b57d726b7","uuid":"0e45b2d4-8589-4beb-9968-5b033f06de90"}
